Mar 24 2009 	Great Service at a Great Hotel	We spent a very pleasant weekend at the Auberge de Vieux Port in mid-March. The room was as presented on the website – the stone wall, wooden posts and wooden floors gave it a unique and romantic character that you will not find in your typical high-rise hotel. The hotel is within walking distance of most of the downtown attractions and key buildings. We walked to and from the train station in about thirty minutes, along the way passing Notre Dame and the convention centre. Supper at the hotel restaurant was excellent, and we enjoyed the jazz duo that plays on weekends. There were also several restaurants catering to a range of tastes and prices on St. Paul Street, directly behind the hotel.  The price was also as presented, with no surprises at checkout time.The room came with a Jacuzzi tub, but unfortunately it was only built for one. (Well, two people could fit if you are both small.) We prefer a firm mattress, so we found the bed to be very comfortable.The only negative was that noise from the street level easily drifts up and through the window, so be warned if you are prone to retiring early. However, what struck us most was the very attentive service, and the outgoing, enthusiastic and friendly attitude of the hotel staff, making this one of the most pleasant stays at any hotel we have visited.	
